--- Файл №3 ---
Путь: assets\blockbuster\blockstates\director.json
--------------------
{
    "variants": {
        "hidden=false,playing=true": { "model": "blockbuster:director_play" },
        "hidden=false,playing=false": { "model": "blockbuster:director_stop" },
        "hidden=true,playing=true": { "model": "blockbuster:director_play" },
        "hidden=true,playing=false": { "model": "blockbuster:director_stop" }
    }
}

# commands.yml
blockbuster.commands.modelblock.property=§rChanges model block property §7<property>§r to §7<value>§r of a model block at §7<x>§r, §7<y>§r, §7<z>§r.
blockbuster.commands.record.help=§r§oRecord command§r. This command provides few sub-commands for manipulating player recording actions.
blockbuster.commands.model.help=§r§oModel command§r. This command provides sub-commands for managing custom models.
blockbuster.commands.record.remove_all=§rRemoves all actions in player recording by §7<filename>§r
blockbuster.commands.action.append=§rRecords an action from current player into given §7<filename>§r with §7<offset>§r tick which will overwrite given frames after given offset tick. You can also optionally specify §7[scene]§r name. Supplying scene name, helps out with synchronizing the actors.
blockbuster.commands.record.dupe=§rThis command duplicates given §7<filename>§r player recording to a new player recording file with given §7<new_filename>§r. §7[overwrite]§r is §7false§r by default, specify §7true§r if you want to overwrite an existing recording
blockbuster.commands.record.delete=§rDeletes the recording file by §7<filename>§r. If you specify §7[force]§r as true, you'll skip confirmation process.
blockbuster.commands.record.merge=§rMerge actions from §7<source>§r into §7<destination>§r. When you set §7[morph_only]§r to §7true§r, the command will only merge morph actions.
blockbuster.commands.record.restore=§rRestores previous version §7<iteration>§r of a player recording by name §7<filename>§r. For example §7/record restore test 1§r will swap §7test.dat§r and §7test.dat~1§r player recording files places.
blockbuster.commands.record.remove_modal=Are you sure you want to remove the actions at the given tick?
blockbuster.commands.action.request=§rRequests an action, named §7<filename>§r, to be loaded from server to current client.
blockbuster.commands.record.clean=§rThis command cleans given §7<property>§r in §7<filename>§r player recording from §7[from]§r tick to §7[to]§r (not including §7[to]§r) tick to the value specified either in §7[value]§r argument (it accepts relative values) or the value at frame §7[from]§r or the first frame.
blockbuster.commands.model.clear_structures=§rClears the structure morphs cache and reloads all of the structures.
blockbuster.commands.record.info=§rOutputs information about player recording by filename §7<filename>§r, such as saved version of record format, length of the record, etc.
blockbuster.commands.record.prolong=§rThis command allows to specify a pre and post delay for given §7<filename>§r player recording.
blockbuster.commands.modelblock.help=§r§oModel block command§r. This command allows editing model blocks through commands.
blockbuster.commands.modelblock.morph=§rChanges morph to §7[morph_nbt]§r of a model block at §7<x>§r, §7<y>§r, §7<z>§r.
blockbuster.commands.record.add=§rAdds an action to player recording by §7<filename>§r at §7<tick>§r of type §7<action_type>§r with additional data specified in §7[data_tag]§r.
blockbuster.commands.record.remove_body_yaw=§rRemoves body yaw properties from given player recording.
blockbuster.commands.model.combine=§rCreates combination of textures specified in §7<paths...>§r (relative to §7config/blockbuster/models/§r) into single skins, and exports them to §7config/blockbuster/export/§r.
blockbuster.commands.damage.help=§rInflicts §7<amount>§r damage to §7<entity>§r. If §7<amount>§r is negative then all §7<entity>§r matched by target selector will be healed.
blockbuster.commands.action.clear=§rRemoves all records on the client (used to force unload client-side records).
blockbuster.commands.action.help=§r§oAction command§r. This command provides few sub-commands for managing player recording actions.
blockbuster.commands.record.remove_all_modal=Are you sure you want to remove all actions in the recording "%s"?
blockbuster.commands.record.remove=§rRemoves all actions on §7<tick>§r in player recording by §7<filename>§r. If you'll specify §7[index]§r, command will remove only one action in §7<tick>§r at §7[index]§r. §7[index]§r of -1 deletes all actions in §7<tick>§r. If you specify §7[force]§r as true, you'll skip confirmation process.
blockbuster.commands.action.cancel=§rCancels currently recording action.
blockbuster.commands.item_nbt.help=§rItem NBT command allows to copy current held item's NBT tag to the clipboard. If you provide §7<give_command>§r as §7true§r or §71§r it will copy to clipboard a proper §7/give§r command to give that item. You'll most likely need a command block for that...
blockbuster.commands.action.play=§rPlaybacks an action from given §7<filename>§r. This sub-command also can receive optional arguments §7[invincibility]§r flag (§71§r, §70§r, §7true§r or §7false§r values) and §7[morph_nbt]§r (which allows to specify a morph).
blockbuster.commands.scene=§rStart, stop or toggle playback of scene by §7<name>§r. There is also §7loop§r which allow to change looping with §7[flag]§r argument (§7true§r or §7false§r).
blockbuster.commands.record.cut=§rThis command removes all actions in player recording §7<filename>§r before §7<before>§r and after §7<after>§r (pre and post delays shouldn't be taken into account giving §7<from>§r and §7<to>§r arguments).
blockbuster.commands.record.reverse=§rReverses the order of frames and actions in the player recording by name §7<filename>§r.
blockbuster.commands.model.convert=§rConverts a skin §7<skin>§r (name filename without extension in §7<steve|fred>§r model) 64x64 (§7fred§r) to 64x32 or 64x32 (§7steve§r) to 64x64 skin.
blockbuster.commands.record.fill=§rThis command inserts §7<count>§f frames at §7[tick]§f in §7<filename>§r player recording. If §7[tick]§r is not provided, it would use the length of given player recording.
blockbuster.commands.model.reload=§rForces the client and server to reload models (server-side only for OP users) with optional §7[force]§r argument which if is §7true§r will reload all models surpassing cached non-modified files timestamp.
blockbuster.commands.record.erase=§rThis command removes §7<count>§r actions in player recording §7<filename>§r starting at tick §7<from>§r.
blockbuster.commands.record.fade=§rThis command fades out §7<filename>§r player recording to the first frame using linear interpolation that fades §7<fade_out>§r ticks.
blockbuster.commands.model.export_obj=§rConverts Blockbuster JSON model named §7<model_name>§r to OBJ (along side with default texture, if present, and MTL file). Exported OBJ model can be found in Blockbuster's config §lexport§r folder.
blockbuster.commands.record.process=§rThis command processes given §7<property>§r in §7<filename>§r player recording from §7<from>§r tick to §7<to>§r and applies given §7<math>§r expression. Following variables are available:\n\n§7initial§r - initial value of given property\n§7value§r - current value of given property\n§7tick§r - currently processing frame's tick\n§7from§r - §7<from>§r argument\n§7to§r - §7<to>§r argument\n§7factor§r - how far into the processing the expression between §7from§r and §7to§r is (0..1), the formula for it is basically §7(tick - from) / (to - from)§r\n
blockbuster.commands.record.create=§rThis command creates a player recording named §7<filename>§r with §7<duration>§r frames. §7[x]§r, §7[y]§r, §7[z]§r, §7[yaw]§r, and §7[pitch]§r can be optionally specified to override current sender's position and rotation (relative §7~§r values are supported).
blockbuster.commands.record.get=§rOutputs data tag of action found at §7<tick>§r in player recording by filename §7<filename>§r.
blockbuster.commands.model.report=§rThis command creates a report about which models and skins are present, and which loaded by Minecraft, and copies it to the copy-paste buffer. This command is for assistance purposes only.
blockbuster.commands.on_head.help=§r§oOn head command§r. This command allows putting currently held item in the main slot directly in the head slot, without any hassle of coming up with NBT data tag.
blockbuster.commands.spectate.help=§r§oSpectate command§r. This command allows making given §7<player>§r to spectate given §7<entity>§r.
blockbuster.commands.record.apply=§rApplies §7<source>§r's frames list of §7<properties>§r (can be separated by §7,§r) on §7<target>§r player recording. Optionally you can specify whether frame properties will be applied §7[relative]§r (by default absolutely), and you can specify the range from §7[from]§r to §7[to]§r ticks.\n\nAdditionally special types like §7head
blockbuster.commands.record.flip=§rThis command flips frames and actions of §7<filename>§r player recording across given §7<axis>§r at given §7<coordinate>§r. Set §7[center]§r to §7false§r (by default it's §7true§r) if you're mirroring across even number of blocks thick wall.
blockbuster.commands.record.delete_modal=Are you sure you want to delete the "%s" recording file?
blockbuster.commands.mount.help=§r§oMount command§r. This command allows making given §7<target>§r entity to mount a given §7[destination]§r entity. If §7[destination]§r is omitted, then the §7<target>§r will be dismounted.\n\nMake sure there are only one entity that is qualifies for §7<target>§r and §7[destination]§r target selectors!
blockbuster.commands.record.search=§rSearches for actions, optionally limited by §7[limit]§r, of given §7<action_type>§r and outputs the tick and, optionally output data tag, found in player recording by filename §7<filename>§r.
blockbuster.commands.action.record=§rRecords an action from current player into given §7<filename>§r. You can also optionally specify §7[scene]§r name. Supplying scene name, helps out with synchronizing the actors.
blockbuster.commands.record.tp=§rThis command teleports player to first frame or frame at §7[tick]§r frame, if specified, §7<filename>§r player recording.
blockbuster.commands.record.camera=§rGenerates a new (or updates exisitng) player recording named §7<filename>§r using the the data from server side §7<camera_profile>§r. Optional offset §7[x]§r, §7[y]§r and §7[z]§r can be provided that will shift the position by given XYZ offset.
blockbuster.commands.action.stop=§rStops the recording of action. If the player didn't record anything, nothing will happen.
blockbuster.commands.record.rename=§rThis command renames given §7<filename>§r player recording to a new name §7<new_filename>§r. It also renames past versions of the §7<filename>§r player recording, if there are any.
blockbuster.commands.model.clear=§rClears the texture cache from loaded Blockbuster's skin textures. If §7[path]§r specified, the command will only clear the textures which begins with §7[path]§r.
blockbuster.commands.model.export=§rExports model from §7<entity_name>§r mob renderer in JSON format that actor use for custom models. This model will be exported into export folder of Blockbuster's config folder. Optionally you can provide §7[entity_tag]§r to generate a model from entity with specific data.\n\n§r§lAttention§r: those models are automatically generated and aren't perfect. You'll need to adjust those models in McME to get best result.\n
blockbuster.commands.record.calculate_body_yaw=§rAutomatically calculates body yaw for given player recording§r.
blockbuster.commands.record.origin=§rThis command changes the origin (the first frame) of the player recording according to §7[x] [y] [z]§r (if all three were specified) or player's current position. You might also rotate the player recording across Y axis relative to its first frame.

# config_comments.yml
blockbuster.config.comments.snowstorm.depth_sorting=When enabled is fixes the particles being seen behind other semi-transparent particles. This option is very performance intensive, consider it using only when rendering video footage
blockbuster.config.comments.audio.waveform_height=Height of an audio bar in pixels
blockbuster.config.comments.audio.waveform_filename=Whether filename of the played audio in the audio should be shown
blockbuster.config.comments.audio.waveform_width=Width of an audio bar in floating point percentage (between 0 and 1)
blockbuster.config.comments.audio.audio_sync=Whether the audio should always try to sync between server and client. This does not affect the playback and syncing when rejoining on a server with running audio. This option is for starting audio playback while being on the server. This configuration is a server side option.
blockbuster.config.comments.recording.record_pause_preview=This option enabled preview of animated morphs like image morph animations, animated poses, record morphs and sequencers. It's affects performance of the server side.
blockbuster.config.comments.audio.waveform_visible=Whether audio bars should be shown when they're playing back
blockbuster.config.comments.damage_control.damage_control=Whether damage control is enabled
blockbuster.config.comments.actor.actor_always_render=Make actor always rendered, no matter where it is or its hitbox size
blockbuster.config.comments.damage_control.damage_control_distance=Radius of effect for damage control
blockbuster.config.comments.model_block.model_block_missing_name_rendering=Render the path of models if they are missing. They will always render in F3 mode.
blockbuster.config.comments.recording.recording_countdown=Recording countdown (in seconds)
blockbuster.config.comments.recording.record_unload_time=How long does it take to unload a record (in ticks)
blockbuster.config.comments.onion_skin.morph_action_color=Display the previous morph during editing
blockbuster.config.comments.scenes.save_update=Whether scenes should be reloaded, if running, after saving the scene by exiting the dashboard GUI.
blockbuster.config.comments.recording.record_attack_on_swipe=Does attack action get recorded with swipe action?
blockbuster.config.comments.actor.actor_y=Makes actors use correct Y value (fixes issue with hovering and jumping, but makes Y movement sharp)
blockbuster.config.comments.model_folders.path=Absolute path to additional model Folder (on windows add the drive letter)
blockbuster.config.comments.immersive_editor.model_block=Whether to use the immersive editor for model block
blockbuster.config.comments.recording.record_render_debug_paths=Enable the rendering of recording debug paths.
blockbuster.config.comments.model_block.reset_on_playback=When enabled, once a scene starts playing all playback, all model blocks will reset themselves
blockbuster.config.comments.recording.record_chat_prefix=Prefix which will get prepended to the actual message in the chat action (%%NAME%% wild card supported for current actor's name)
blockbuster.config.comments.general.bb_gun_sync_distance=If it's greater than 0, this option enables BB gun projectile synchronization, which makes projectile sync with the server, but at the cost of jittery teleportation
blockbuster.config.comments.actor.actor_tracking_range=How far actors are tracked? Requires restart of the game.
blockbuster.config.comments.model_block.model_block_debug_rendering_f1=Render the debug cube of model blocks while being in F1 mode, alongside F3 mode.
blockbuster.config.comments.recording.record_sync_rate=How often a recording is going to synchronize with the server?
blockbuster.config.comments.recording.record_unload=Enable automatic record unloading?
blockbuster.config.comments.audio.waveform_density=How many pixels of audio waveform should be shown per second
blockbuster.config.comments.better_lights.enable_better_lights=Enable the Better Lights lightcaster in all morphs. You still need the Better Lights Mod.
blockbuster.config.comments.model_block.model_block_disable_rendering=Whether model blocks should be rendered

blockbuster.commands.record.prolong=§l§6/§rrecord §8prolong§r §7<filename> [post_delay] [pre_delay]§r\n\n§rCette commande permet d'ajouter plus de temps au début ou à la fin de l'enregistrement de l'acteur §7<filename>§r.\n            \n
blockbuster.commands.record.add=§l§6/§rrecord §8add§r §7<filename> <tick> <action_type> [data_tag]§r\n\n§rAjoute une action à l'enregistrement l'acteur §7<filename>§r au tick §7<tick>§r de type §7<action_type>§r et de données complémentaires §7[data_tag]§r.\n
blockbuster.commands.record.search=§l§6/§rrecord §8search§r §7<filename> <action_type> [limit] [output_tags]§r\n\n§rRecherche dans l'enregistrement de l'acteur §7<filename>§r les actions dont le type est §7<action_type>§r dans la limite (en option) §7[limit]§r, et affiche les ticks où elles sont enregistrées ainsi que les données associées.\n
blockbuster.commands.action.record=§l§6/§raction §8record§r §7<filename> [x] [y] [z]§7\n\n§rLance l'enregistrement de l'acteur §7<filename>§r. Si les coordonnées du director block §7[x]§f, §7[y]§f et §7[z]§f sont précisées, les actions des autres acteurs présents dans ce directorblock sont jouées durant l'enregistrement)\n
blockbuster.commands.record.tp=§l§6/§rrecord §8tp§r §7<filename> [tick]§r\n\n§rCette commande permet de se téléporter à la position de l'acteur §7<filename>§r au début de son enregistrement ou au tick §7[tick]§r (en option).\n
blockbuster.commands.action.stop=§l§6/§raction §8stop§r\n\n§rArrête l'enregistrement des actions.\n
blockbuster.commands.action.clear=§l§6/§raction §8clear§r\n\n§rSupprime tous les enregistrement côté client (utilisé pour forcer le déchargement des enregistrements côté client).\n
blockbuster.commands.action.help=§r§oAction command§r. Cette commande founie des sous-commandes pour la gestion des actions enregistrées.
blockbuster.commands.record.remove=§l§6/§rrecord §8remove§r §7<filename> <tick> [index]§r\n\n§rSupprime toutes les actions au tick §7<tick>§r dans l'enregistrement de l'acteur §7<filename>§r sur tous les index (Toutes les lignes). En spécifiant l'index §7[index]§r (= la ligne dans l'éditeur d'actions), la commande supprime uniquement l'action au tick §7<tick>§r à l'index §7[index]§r.\n
blockbuster.commands.model.clear=§l§6/§rmodel §8clear§r §7[path]§r\n\n§rEfface le cache des textures chargées dans Blockbuster. Si §7[path]§r est spécifié, cette commande effacera uniquement les textures qui commencent par §7[path]§r.\n
blockbuster.commands.director=§l§6/§rdirector §8<play|toggle|stop|loop|disable_state>§r §7<x> <y> <z> [flag]§r\n\n§rDémarre, arrête  ou bascule (on/off) le director block positionné en  §7<x>§r, §7<y>§r, et §7<z>§r (Utiliser la touche F3 pour connaitre les coordonnées). Utiliser §7loop§r pour une lecture en boucle et §7disable_state§r pour la sortie Restone (sur les côtés du director block) en changeant leur §7[flag]§r valeur par (§7true§r ou §7false§r).\n
blockbuster.commands.model.export=§l§6/§rmodel §8export§r §7<entity_name> [entity_tag]§r\n\n§rExporte le modèle §7<entity_name>§r au format JSON. Le modèle est exporté dans le dossier export du dossier ".minecraft\config\blockbuster\export\". Utiliser §7[entity_tag]§r pour exporter un model avec des données en option.\n\n§r§lAttention§r: l'exportation de modèles présente parfois des erreurs. Des corrections avec l'outil McME (https://mchorse.github.io/mcme/) sont parfois nécessaires.\n
blockbuster.commands.action.play=§l§6/§raction §8play§r §7<filename> [name_tag] [model] [skin] [invincibility]§r\n\n§rLance le playback de l'acteur §7<filename>§r. Cette commande a différentes options: le nom de l'acteur §7[name]§r, son modèle §7[model]§r et son skin §7[skin]§r ainsi que son invincibilité §7[invincibility]§r avec les choix (§71§r, §70§r, §7true§r ou §7false§r).\n
blockbuster.commands.model.replace_texture=§l§6/§rmodel §8replace_texture§r §7<target> [replace]§r\n\n§rRemplace une texture §7<target>§r (préciser dans §7<target>§r sa localisation comme b.a:dossier/skin) par une texture §7[replace]§r (préciser dans §7[replace]§r sa localisation comme b.a:nouveau_dossier/nouvelle_skin). Si §7[replace]§r n'est pas précisé, alors la texture §7<target>§r's sera restaurée.\n
blockbuster.commands.record.origin=§l§6/§rrecord §8origin§r §7<filename> [rotation] [x] [y] [z]§r\n\n§rCette commande permet de repositionner un acteur après son enregistrement en spécifiant §7[x] [y] [z]§r (utiliser ~ pour des données relatives). Si §7[x] [y] [z]§r ne sont pas renseignés, l'acteur se repositionne à votre emplacement. §7rotation§r permet de tourner l'acteur en utisant des données relatives.   \n

Опция не влияет на воспроизведение и синхронизацию при перезаходе на сервер во время проигрывания аудио. Эта настройка предназначена для синхронизации начала воспроизведения аудио во время нахождения на сервере. Эта настройка работает на стороне сервера.

# commands.yml
blockbuster.commands.modelblock.property=§rЗмінює властивість §7<property>§r на значення §7<value>§r у блоці-моделі, розташованому у §7<x>§r, §7<y>§r, §7<z>§r.
blockbuster.commands.record.help=§r§oКоманда запису§r. Дана команда команда містить кілька підкоманд для керування діями записів гравця.
blockbuster.commands.model.help=§r§oКоманда моделі§r. Дана команда містить кілька підкоманд для керування користувацькими моделями.
blockbuster.commands.record.remove_all=§rВидаляє усі дії у записі гравця з назвою §7<filename>§r
blockbuster.commands.action.append=§rзаписує дію від поточного гравця до заданого файлу §7<filename>§r зі зміщенням у тіках §7<offset>§r, що перезапише означені кадри після тіку зміщення. Також ви можете додатково вказати назву сцени §7[scene]§r. Якщо ви надасте назву сцени, стане легше синхронізувати акторів.
blockbuster.commands.record.dupe=§rДана команда дублює заданий запис гравця з назвою §7<filename>§r у новий запис гравця з заданою назвою §7<new_filename>§r. Аргумент перезапису §7[overwrite]§r усталено встановлено на §7false§r, але ви можете встановити його на §7true§r у разі якщо бажаєте перезаписати вже існуючий запис
blockbuster.commands.record.delete=§rВидаляє файл запису з назвою §7<filename>§r. У разі якщо аргумент примусу §7[force]§r встановлено на true, процес підтвердження буде пропущено.
blockbuster.commands.record.merge=§rОб'єднує дії з джерела §7<source>§r до призначення §7<destination>§r. Якщо аргумент "лише морфи" §7[morph_only]§r задано на §7true§r, команда об'єднає лише дії морфів.
blockbuster.commands.record.restore=§rВідновлює попередню версію §7<iteration>§r запису гравця з назвою §7<filename>§r. До прикладу, §7/record restore test 1§r поміняє місцями записи гравців §7test.dat§r та §7test.dat~1§r.
blockbuster.commands.record.remove_modal=Ви впевнені, що бажаєте видалити дії у заданому тіці?
blockbuster.commands.action.request=§rЗапитує аби дію, з назвою §7<filename>§r, було завантажено з сервера до поточного клієнту.

blockbuster.commands.record.fade=§r该命令会使用线性插值，淡出玩家回放 §7<文件名>§r 中，时长为 §7<淡出>§r Tick 到第一帧之间的动画。
blockbuster.commands.model.export_obj=§r将名为 §7<模型名称>§r 的 Blockbuster JSON 模型转换为 OBJ 模型（包括默认材质，以及如果存在的 MTL 文件）。导出的 OBJ 模型可以在 Blockbuster 的配置文件夹中的 §lexport§r 文件夹内找到。
blockbuster.commands.record.process=§r该命令会处理玩家回放 §7<文件名>§r 从 §7<起始时间>§r Tick 到 §7<结束时间>§r 中给定的 §7<属性>§r，并应用给定的 §7<数学表达式>§r 表达式。以下是可用的变量:\n\n§7initial§r - 给定属性的初始值\n§7value§r - 给定属性的当前值\n§7tick§r - 当前在处理的帧的 Tick\n§7from§r - §7<起始时间>§r 参数\n§7to§r - §7<结束时间>§r 参数\n§7factor§r - §7起始时间§r 和 §7结束时间§r 之间的表达式进行处理的距离是 (0..1)，它的公式基本上是 §7 (tick - from) / (to - from)§r\n
blockbuster.commands.record.create=§r该命令会创建一个名为 §7<文件名>§r 的玩家回放，并包含 §7<持续时间>§r 帧。您可以选择指定 §7[x]§r、§7[y]§r、§7[z]§r、§7[偏航]§r，以及 §7[俯仰]§r 来覆盖当前命令发送者的位置和旋转信息（支持相对值 §7~§r ）。
blockbuster.commands.record.get=§r输出玩家回放 §7<文件名>§r 文件中，在 §7<tick>§r 处找到的动作数据。
blockbuster.commands.model.report=§r该命令会创建一个关于哪些模型和皮肤存在，以及哪些由 Minecraft 加载的报告，并将其复制到剪贴板。此命令仅用于协助目的。
blockbuster.commands.on_head.help=§r§o戴在头上命令§r。该命令可以将当前主手拿着的物品直接放入头上的物品槽，无需受任何 NBT 标签的困扰。
blockbuster.commands.spectate.help=§r§o观察者命令§r。该命令可以让指定的§7玩家§r附身至指定§7实体§r的视角上。
blockbuster.commands.record.apply=将 §7<source_来源>§r 的帧列表中的 §7<属性>§r（可以使用 §7,§r 进行分隔）应用于 §7<目标>§r 玩家回放。您可以选择指定帧属性是否会被 §7[relative(相对)]§r 应用（默认为绝对），并且您还可以指定从 §7[开始帧]§r 到 §7[结束帧]§r 的 Tick 范围。\n\n另外有一些特殊的属性类型，比如 §7head
blockbuster.commands.record.flip=§r该命令会将玩家回放 §7<文件名>§r 中的帧和动作，沿给定的 §7<轴>§r 和 §7<坐标>§r 翻转。如果您要在方块为偶数厚度的墙面实现镜像效果，请将 §7[中心点]§r 设为 §7false§r（默认是 §7true§r）。
blockbuster.commands.record.delete_modal=您确定要删除 "%s" 回放文件吗？
blockbuster.commands.mount.help=§r§o骑乘命令§r。该命令可以让给定的 §7<目标>§r 实体骑到给定的 §7[骑乘目标]§r 实体上去。若忽略 §7[骑乘目标]§r，则 §7<目标>§r 会取消骑乘。\n\n请确保只有一个实体符合 §7<目标>§r 和 §7[骑乘目标]§r 选择器的条件！
blockbuster.commands.record.search=§r在玩家回放 §7<文件名>§r 中搜索动作给定的 §7<动作类型>§r 动作，可选择用 §7[限制]§r 进行限制，然后输出 Tick 时间，可选择输出哪些数据标签。
blockbuster.commands.action.record=§r将当前玩家的动作录制到玩家回放 §7<文件名>§r 中。您也可以指定 §7[场景]§r。提供场景名称，用于同步演员。

blockbuster.commands.record.camera=§r使用来自服务端的 §7<相机配置>§r 的数据，生成一个新的（或更新现有的）名为 §7<文件名>§r 的玩家回放。也可以提供可选的偏移量 §7[x]§7、§7[y]§7 和 §7[z]§7，这些偏移量将通过给定的 XYZ 偏移量移动回放的位置。
blockbuster.commands.action.stop=§r停止录制动作。若玩家没有录制任何动作，什么都不会发生。
blockbuster.commands.record.rename=§r该命令会将给定的名为 §7<文件名>§r 的玩家回放重新命名为 §7<新文件名>§r。如果回放存在先前版本，该命令也会对前几个版本的回放 <文件名> 进行重命名。
blockbuster.commands.model.clear=§r清除加载的 Blockbuster 皮肤材质的材质缓存。如果指定了 §7[路径]§r，该命令只会清理来自 §7[路径]§r 的材质。
blockbuster.commands.model.export=§r以 JSON 格式导出来自 §7<实体名称>§r 生物渲染群的模型，该格式用于演员所使用的自定义模型。模型将会导出在 Blockbuster 的 config 文件夹的 export 文件夹。您可以选择提供 §7[实体标签]§r 来导出具有特定数据的实体生成模型。\n\n§r§l注意§r: 这些自动生成的模型不完美，您需要在 McME 进一步编辑获得最佳效果。\n
blockbuster.commands.record.calculate_body_yaw=§r自动计算给定玩家回放的偏航值§r。
blockbuster.commands.record.origin=§r该命令会根据 §7[x] [y] [z]§r（如果三个都指定了）来改变玩家回放的原点（第一帧），或者取玩家当前的位置。您也可以将玩家回放的内容相对于第一帧在 Y 轴上进行旋转。

blockbuster.commands.mount.help=§r§o騎乘命令§r。該命令可以讓給定的 §7<目標>§r 實體騎到給定的 §7[騎乘目標]§r 實體上去。若忽略 §7[騎乘目標]§r，則 §7<目標>§r 會取消騎乘。\n\n請確保只有一個實體符合 §7<目標>§r 和 §7[騎乘目標]§r 選擇器的條件！
blockbuster.commands.record.search=§r在玩家回放 §7<文件名>§r 中搜索動作給定的 §7<動作類型>§r 動作，可選擇用 §7[限制]§r 進行限制，然後輸出 Tick 時間，可選擇輸出哪些數據標籤。
blockbuster.commands.action.record=§r將當前玩家的動作錄製到玩家回放 §7<文件名>§r 中。您也可以指定 §7[場景]§r。提供場景名稱，用於同步演員。
blockbuster.commands.record.tp=§r該命令會傳送玩家到名為玩家回放 §7<文件名>§r 的第一幀或指定的第 §7[tick]§r 幀處。
blockbuster.commands.record.camera=§r使用來自服務端的 §7<相機配置>§r 的數據，生成一個新的（或更新現有的）名為 §7<文件名>§r 的玩家回放。也可以提供可選的偏移量 §7[x]§7、§7[y]§7 和 §7[z]§7，這些偏移量將通過給定的 XYZ 偏移量移動回放的位置。
blockbuster.commands.action.stop=§r停止錄製動作。若玩家沒有錄製任何動作，什麼都不會發生。
blockbuster.commands.record.rename=§r該命令會將給定的名為 §7<文件名>§r 的玩家回放重新命名為 §7<新文件名>§r。如果回放存在先前版本，該命令也會對前幾個版本的回放 <文件名> 進行重命名。
blockbuster.commands.model.clear=§r清除加載的 Blockbuster 皮膚材質的材質緩存。如果指定了 §7[路徑]§r，該命令只會清理來自 §7[路徑]§r 的材質。
blockbuster.commands.model.export=§r以 JSON 格式導出來自 §7<實體名稱>§r 生物渲染群的模型，該格式用於演員所使用的自定義模型。模型將會導出在 Blockbuster 的 config 文件夾的 export 文件夾。您可以選擇提供 §7[實體標籤]§r 來導出具有特定數據的實體生成模型。\n\n§r§l注意§r: 這些自動生成的模型不完美，您需要在 McME 進一步編輯獲得最佳效果。\n
blockbuster.commands.record.calculate_body_yaw=§r自動計算給定玩家回放的偏航值§r。
blockbuster.commands.record.origin=§r該命令會根據 §7[x] [y] [z]§r（如果三個都指定了）來改變玩家回放的原點（第一幀），或者取玩家當前的位置。您也可以將玩家回放的內容相對於第一幀在 Y 軸上進行旋轉。

--- Файл №62 ---
Путь: assets\blockbuster\models\user\README.txt
--------------------
In this folder, you can place your own models in order to "pack" them into 
Blockbuster mod's jar. Automatically it won't work though, you'll need to 
edit the user.json file, and add there the models you're going to use, 
specify if OBJ, MTL, OBJ shapes or VOX files paths relative to users folder
and also change the paths to point into Blockbuster's jar path.

The JSON format for user.json is something like this:

{
    "siren_head": {
        "obj": "Siren_head.obj"
    },
    "shrek": {
        "obj": "model.obj",
        "mtl": "model.mtl",
        "shapes": [
            "shapes/smile.obj"
        ]
    },
    "lego": {
        "obj": "lego.obj",
        "mtl": "lego.mtl"
    },
    "book": {
        "vox": "book.vox"
    }
}

It's pretty hard to explain the entire thing, but if you'll stumble upon this 
file and will be have issues with packing your models into the mod's jar, feel 
free to join my Discord server and ask me about this: https://discord.gg/qfxrqUF

==================================================

--- Файл №63 ---
Путь: assets\blockbuster\optifine\dynamic_lights.properties
--------------------
###############################################################################
# Sample configuration for OptiFine's Dynamic Lights feature.
###############################################################################
# dynamic_lights.properties
###############################################################################
# This file is offered without any copyright restrictions.
# Please copy and modify it to suit your needs.
#
# This configuration file allows mods to define dynamic light levels for entities and items.
# Location: "/assets/<mod_id>/optifine/dynamic_lights.properties"

# Entity light levels
# The entity name is automatically expanded with the mod_id.
# The light level should be between 0 and 15.
# For exaple:
#   entities=basalz:15 blitz:7
#entities=<entity:light> ...

# Item light levels
# The item name is automatically expanded with the mod_id.
# The light level should be between 0 and 15.
# For exaple:
#   items=florb:15 morb:7
items=model1:1 model2:2 model3:3 model4:4 model5:5 model6:6 model7:7 model8:8 model9:9 model10:10 model11:11 model12:12 model13:13 model14:14 model15:15

{
	"format_version": "1.10.0",
	"particle_effect": {
		"description": {
			"identifier": "snowstorm:fire",
			"basic_render_parameters": {
				"material": "particles_alpha",
				"texture": "minecraft:textures/blocks/fire_layer_1.png"
			}
		},
		"components": {
			"minecraft:emitter_rate_steady": {
				"spawn_rate": 20,
				"max_particles": 1000
			},
			"minecraft:emitter_lifetime_looping": {
				"active_time": 1
			},
			"minecraft:emitter_shape_disc": {
				"offset": [0, 0.4, 0],
				"radius": 1.2,
				"direction": "outwards"
			},
			"minecraft:particle_lifetime_expression": {
				"max_lifetime": "Math.random(1, 1.4)"
			},
			"minecraft:particle_initial_speed": 1,
			"minecraft:particle_motion_dynamic": {
				"linear_acceleration": ["(variable.particle_random_1-0.5)", 1.2, "(variable.particle_random_1-0.5)"]
			},
			"minecraft:particle_appearance_billboard": {
				"size": [0.4, 0.4],
				"facing_camera_mode": "lookat_xyz",
				"uv": {
					"texture_width": 16,
					"texture_height": 512,
					"flipbook": {
						"base_UV": [0, 0],
						"size_UV": [16, 16],
						"step_UV": [0, 16],
						"max_frame": 32,
						"stretch_to_lifetime": true
					}
				}
			}
		}
	}
